               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420404-name-1476" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1476" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1476" type="surname" value="PONFOLD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420404-name-1476" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM PONFOLD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am master of the <hi rend="italic">Minx</hi> schooner, lying in the Green Dock, Rotherhithe on the 8th of March, I shipped the prisoner on <hi rend="italic">the</hi> 3rd, at the wharf—I left him in care of the ship on the 4th of March—I returned on the 8th to get my clothes, and missed my quadrant—I taxed the prisoner with it—he said he knew nothing about it—I over-hauled my clothes, and missed the articles stated—I went to the Thames-police, and on the 9th, I went on board again—the prisoner was then gone—I found him on the 15th—he had my waistcoat and shirt on, which I had missed—these now produced are mine—some have my name on them in full—they were all in the ship when I left him in charge—I have not found the quadrant.</p>
